Spectral Workbench is a web application built on Ruby on Rails and JavaScript. It allows you to upload images you've taken of spectra (using a DIY spectrometer: http://publiclab.org/wiki/spectrometer) and generate graphs for analysis. By Jeffrey Warren (http://publiclab.org/profile/warren)

=============================================================

You can see it in action at: http://spectralworkbench.org

This project started in the Environmental Justice research cluster at RISD's Digital+Media department, run by Sara Wylie and Jeff Warren. It is now part of the Public Laboratory for Open Technology and Science's civic science toolkit.

=============================================================

Read more about our experiments and work here: http://publiclab.org

